The massive drone attack on Kyiv Oblast is continuing. Dozens of explosions have been heard in Kyiv, Bucha, Bila Tservka, etc. 
There are still around 40 Geran-2 drones detected in Ukrainian airspace.

Security camera footage showing some of the Russian Kh-101 missile strikes, and Ukrainian Patriot interceptor launches in Kyiv earlier.

Large fires are burning in Kyiv following the large-scale missile attack on the city. At least 9 Kh-101 cruise missiles impacted. 
There is significant damage to civilian infrastructure, however, likely the result the Patriot and Kh-101 debris falling, as 6 missiles were shot down above Kyiv's suburbs (although the cause of this damage can be confirmed later once clearer footage is published).

At least 6 Ukrainian HIMARS rockets impacted the main power plant in Belgorod. Power outages were reported across Belgorod city and the surrounding areas. Media 1 shows the HIMARS rockets being launched from within Kharkiv City.

Last night, Ukrainian ATACMS ballistic missiles struck the Karachevsky plant in the city of Karachev, Bryansk Oblast. It specialises in production of electrical connectors, cable products, electro-technical components, and electronic warfare equipment. 
The fires pictured are in the plant's workshops. 
Coordinates: 53.127038, 35.008618

Following the Ukrainian ATACMS ballistic missile strikes on Bryansk Oblast, U.S. Special Envoy to Ukraine Keith Kellogg confirmed that Trump has authorised Ukraine to carry out long-range strikes into Russia. 
Last year, after winning the election, Trump called Biden's decision to allow long-range strikes using western weaponry "stupid" and a "mistake".
